.TH "hw_cfg_wol" 9 "hw_cfg_wol" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hw_cfg_wol \- configure Wake-on-LAN features
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hw_cfg_wol
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 frame "  ","
.BI "int set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "frame" 12
The pattern frame bit.
.IP "set" 12
The flag indicating whether to enable or disable.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is used to enable or disable certain Wake-on-LAN features.
